HEADWORD: Gynæcophore
<hw>Gy*n⟦ae⟧"co*phore</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧*n⟦emac⟧"k⟦osl⟧*f⟦omac⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>gynaikei^on</grk> the women's apartments +
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A ventral
canal or groove, in which the males of some di⟦oe⟧cious trematodes carry
the female. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>H⟦ae⟧matozoa</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

